description: Recently sold: $255,000. This historic home was built for city founder Edward Phalen, and passed off to Edmund Rice... maybe you've heard of them; their namesakes (Lake Phalen and Rice Street) are just blocks away. This home retains natural woodwork, solid doors, hardwood floors, and very high ceilings. It has a huge yard, an unbeatable view of the city, and is reputed to be one of the highest points in St.Paul. It has an oversized, heated 3-car garage with pull-down stairs for storage. New driveway and patio (2018), siding (2016); real fireplaces (one with original, ornate stonework), 3 pellet stoves (main level, attic, garage). This property has been licensed for rental and is set up to be two independent units. The main entryway can be used to access the top and bottom units separately, and independently. Main level, there are 2 bed, a 3/4 bath, a 4-season porch, and a kitchen, living and dining room. Second level, 2 bed, full bath, kitchen/living, and full attic bedroom.
